\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Defoe's student and reviewer as a militant JWL}, in a photograph taken around 2023 in Entebbe, Uganda, at a popular spot near the Victorian waters. This scene perhaps, among his gun-wielding moments ever, might be the closest experience the reviewer has, for a documented moment wielding a gun around other people, though, as might be clear from the photograph, it \textbf  {wasn't in a moment of distress} such as Defoe is currently talking about, and neither did he need to fire it even if it was surely loaded. Interesting to note too, past that moment, his eldest son quickly picked interest in the gun, and having unceasingly cried for it, the father gave it to him. It is on record then, that \textbf  {Theo R. Willrich} --- whose mother, also a \textit  {Munyakitara}, without doubt, as close to the lady shown in this photograph as can be [during her younger years] --- currently keeps this particularly \textbf  {special elite gun.}}}{18}{figure.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
