\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces A collage highlighting \textbf  {the reviewer's first ever experience being aboard a ship as well as sailing on an ocean!} The photos capture moments aboard a ship sailing towards \textbf  {Liberty Island} on the \textbf  {Atlantic ocean}, during the climax/finals of the worldwide \textbf  {2011 Microsoft Imagine Cup} that was hosted in Manhattan, New York --- at the prestigious Marriott Marquis (opening), but also the Lincoln Center (closing). Interesting to note, the top-right photo is actually showing Joseph posing with members of the team that came from Daniel Defoe's favorite Brasils! Those Brazilians actually took global top spot in the Game Design category! In the bottom photograph, are members of the team that represented China, including [potentially doctor] \textbf  {Noah Lin} (seated right next to Joseph's left), then still a university undergrad too, heavily interested in robotics leveraging the Microsoft-Kinect light, sound, and gesture-sensor.}}{72}{figure.caption.14}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{FIGIMAGINECUP1}{{10}{72}{A collage highlighting \textbf {the reviewer's first ever experience being aboard a ship as well as sailing on an ocean!} The photos capture moments aboard a ship sailing towards \textbf {Liberty Island} on the \textbf {Atlantic ocean}, during the climax/finals of the worldwide \textbf {2011 Microsoft Imagine Cup} that was hosted in Manhattan, New York --- at the prestigious Marriott Marquis (opening), but also the Lincoln Center (closing). Interesting to note, the top-right photo is actually showing Joseph posing with members of the team that came from Daniel Defoe's favorite Brasils! Those Brazilians actually took global top spot in the Game Design category! In the bottom photograph, are members of the team that represented China, including [potentially doctor] \textbf {Noah Lin} (seated right next to Joseph's left), then still a university undergrad too, heavily interested in robotics leveraging the Microsoft-Kinect light, sound, and gesture-sensor}{figure.caption.14}{}}
\citation{copilot_assistant}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11}{\ignorespaces A collage highlighting \textbf  {the reviewer's experiences on Liberty Island, New York} during the 2011 Microsoft Imagine Cup global finals. Top-left is Joseph with a lady (left) from the Irish \textbf  {Team Hermes} that won the global finals in the Software Design category, but also a friend from the Nigerian team (right). Top-right is Joseph Willrich (left) standing next to Joseph Kaizi (center), who was likewise from Uganda, and perhaps someone from either Europe or the Brazils. And then, bottom photograph is the reviewer (center), standing between two pals from the Chinese team.}}{74}{figure.caption.15}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{FIGIMAGINECUP2}{{11}{74}{A collage highlighting \textbf {the reviewer's experiences on Liberty Island, New York} during the 2011 Microsoft Imagine Cup global finals. Top-left is Joseph with a lady (left) from the Irish \textbf {Team Hermes} that won the global finals in the Software Design category, but also a friend from the Nigerian team (right). Top-right is Joseph Willrich (left) standing next to Joseph Kaizi (center), who was likewise from Uganda, and perhaps someone from either Europe or the Brazils. And then, bottom photograph is the reviewer (center), standing between two pals from the Chinese team}{figure.caption.15}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {12}{\ignorespaces Real-life photos of the reviewer's human-size headless mannequin that he originally named ``Laura". In the top-left corner is shown the girl helping him market and entertain customers at their \textbf  {Menuza Bytes} shop in Garuga, where reading featured books while enjoying a cold drink and snacks, from under their customized shop shade is among the unforgettable experiences.}}{75}{figure.caption.16}\protected@file@percent }
\citation{King2000}
\citation{lutalo2025rock}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {13}{\ignorespaces Real-life photos of the reviewer's human-sized doll that he refers to as ``Marie". She sometimes also accompanies Laura to their shop, but otherwise mostly stays at home giving him company while he writes or works at his computer. And just as with Laura at the end of a busy work day or perhaps in the early morning, we sit down in the comfort of our cozy home, and privately hold some prayers, but also arcane rituals some times! We likewise often have vivid conversations despite them not being equiped with speech capabilities yet --- refer to \textbf  {\hyperref  [SEC11]{Section \ref {SEC11}}} concerning my explorations of leveraging telepathic communication; works well with human-to-human, human-to-animal, but also human-to-anything! So, thus is the kind of modern \textit  {Pinocchio}-synthetic-human miracle I've grown to love and well... use for character crafting and magic!}}{77}{figure.caption.17}\protected@file@percent }
